9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 96, L.D. 163, “An Act to Require Health
10 Insurance Coverage for Federally Approved Nonprescription Oral Hormonal
11 Contraceptives and Nonprescription Emergency Contraceptives”
12 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 4 in paragraph E in the 6th line (page 1, line
13 43 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "pharmacy" the following: 'counter'
14 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 4 in paragraph E in the last 3 lines (page 2,
15 lines 2 to 4 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "The pharmacy may use a standing order
16 to facilitate billing for a nonprescription oral hormonal contraceptive or nonprescription
17 emergency contraceptive in accordance with this paragraph."
18 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 4 by inserting after paragraph E the following:
19 'F. The superintendent shall monitor compliance with the requirements for coverage
20 of nonprescription oral hormonal contraceptives and nonprescription emergency
21 contraceptives and any rules adopted in accordance with subsection 5, including any
22 complaints or barriers to implementation.'
23 Amend the bill in section 5 in subsection 3 in paragraph F in the 5th line (page 3, line
24 10 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "purchase" the following: 'at the pharmacy
25 counter'
26 Amend the bill in section 5 in subsection 3 in paragraph F in the last 4 lines (page 3,
27 lines 11 to 14 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "The pharmacy may use a standing
28 order to facilitate billing for a nonprescription oral hormonal contraceptive or
29 nonprescription emergency contraceptive in accordance with this paragraph."
30 Amend the bill in section 5 in subsection 3 by inserting after paragraph F the following:
31 'G. The superintendent shall monitor compliance with the requirements for coverage
32 of nonprescription oral hormonal contraceptives and nonprescription emergency
33 contraceptives and any rules adopted in accordance with subsection 4, including any
34 complaints or barriers to implementation.'
